						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the Paṭṭābhirāmasvāmin shrine in the Viśvanāthasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 22: 1091-92 A.D.</p>						

						<p>On palaeographical grounds this inscription may be assigned to the 11th century and hence the king may be identified with Kulōttuṅga I.</p>						

						<p>This records the undertaking given by the <hi rend="italic">anvayattār</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">brahmachārins (māṇ-śeydār)</hi> of the temple to burn a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp with the interest accruing from 2 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> received from Nittal Kiḷaiyōmbi, the headman of Vāyaṟṟūr, a merchant residing at Toṭṭiyam.</p>						

						</summary>
